During a press briefing, Sarah Sanders, the White House Press Secretary, discussed the repatriation of the remains of U.S. soldiers from the Korean War, as well as ongoing efforts to account for missing Department of Defense personnel from previous wars. She also addressed questions about President Trump's recent tweets about former White House aide Omarosa Manigault Newman, saying that the President is frustrated with her lack of integrity. Sanders also defended the President against accusations of racism, citing his policies and actions that have benefited African Americans and Hispanics.